The Independent Electoral Commission (IEC) in KwaZulu-Natal will on Tuesday meet with journalists and editors ahead of next year’s national elections. The information sharing session is expected to update the media on the latest plans and developments. The IEC in KwaZulu-Natal will meet journalists to present a working report ahead of next year’s national election. Eligible voters only have one more chance to update their addresses on the voter’s roll and to register to vote ahead of next year. The final voter registration weekend is on January 26 and 27. 